                                								<div class="postavatar">
								<img src="http://sweatnspice.com//wp-content/plugins/post-avatar/images/tongueburner.gif" width="60" height="81" alt="hot-sauce-stains-implicate-man-in-robbery" />
<br />
                                <span class="author">Posted By:<br />TongueBurner</span></div>
                                			<p><a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/downloads/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/6a00d83451d24369e20133ecca978e970b.gif');"  href="http://sweatnspice.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/6a00d83451d24369e20133ecca978e970b.gif"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-2639" title="6a00d83451d24369e20133ecca978e970b" src="http://sweatnspice.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/6a00d83451d24369e20133ecca978e970b.gif" alt="" width="160" height="217" /></a>William Horton should have been a dry rub man.</p>
<p>After a burglary of cologne, sunglasses and a generator last week left a Memphis apartment ransacked with several broken hot sauce bottles, police scoured the neighborhoods looking for the thief.</p>
<p><a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/www.upi.com/Odd_News/2010/04/18/Hot-sauce-leads-to-burglary-suspect/UPI-59181271619434/');"  href="http://www.upi.com/Odd_News/2010/04/18/Hot-sauce-leads-to-burglary-suspect/UPI-59181271619434/  " target="_blank">They found Horton</a>, at right, and arrested him because he was <em>wearing clothes stained with hot sauce.</em></p>
<p><em> </em></p>
<p>He faces charges of theft and aggravated burglary.</p>
<p><span style="font-family: Helvetica, 'Times New Roman', 'Bitstream Charter', Times, serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', 'Bitstream Charter', Times, serif;"><br />
</span></span></span></p>
