<br />
                                <span class="author">Posted By:<br />TongueBurner</span></div>
                                			<p><a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/downloads/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mushroom-pancake-salad.jpg');"  href="http://sweatnspice.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mushroom-pancake-salad.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-2623" title="mushroom pancake salad" src="http://sweatnspice.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mushroom-pancake-salad.jpg" alt="" width="280" height="198" /></a>Fans of hot sauce can only use their favorite sauces on wings, ribs, eggs, dips, etc. so many times before, well, they start getting a little bored.</p>
<p>Thankfully <a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/weblogs.baltimoresun.com/features/green/2010/03/meatless_monday_mushroom_panca.html');"  href="http://weblogs.baltimoresun.com/features/green/2010/03/meatless_monday_mushroom_panca.html" target="_blank">this recipe from the Baltimore Sun&#8217;s B&#8217;More Green blog</a> gives hot sauce lovers a new, tasty alternative: <a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/weblogs.baltimoresun.com/features/green/2010/03/meatless_monday_mushroom_panca.html');"  href="http://weblogs.baltimoresun.com/features/green/2010/03/meatless_monday_mushroom_panca.html" target="_blank">Mushroom Pancake Salad</a>.</p>
<p>It only requires a teaspoon of hot sauce, but the tastes of savory mushroom pancakes, fresh vegetables and the Greek yogurt makes a mouth water just by mention alone. We&#8217;re thinking a garlicky or herb-based sauce would be best as something very peppery might overpower the dish. Take a look at the <a href="http://sweatnspice.com/products-page/marie-sharps-hot-sauces" target="_blank">Marie Sharp&#8217;s line</a> or the <a href="http://sweatnspice.com/products-page/green-bandit-hot-sauces" target="_blank">herb-based Green Bandit sauces</a> for inspiration.</p>
<p><a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/weblogs.baltimoresun.com/features/green/2010/03/meatless_monday_mushroom_panca.html');"  href="http://weblogs.baltimoresun.com/features/green/2010/03/meatless_monday_mushroom_panca.html" target="_blank">See the recipe and the directions here.</a></p>
			</div>
            <br style="clear: both;height: 0px;" />
		</div>

		
		<div class="post" id="post-2618">
			<div class="post-title">
			<p class="post-edit" style="float:right;"></p>
			<h2>
				<a href="http://sweatnspice.com/promotion/talk-show-host-drinks-hot-sauce-for-charity" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent link to Talk show host drinks hot sauce for charity">
				Talk show host drinks hot sauce for charity</a>
			</h2>
			</div>
			
			<div class="post-footer">
			<h4>
				<span class="post-date">April 17th, 2010</span>
				<span class="post-comments"><a href="http://sweatnspice.com/promotion/talk-show-host-drinks-hot-sauce-for-charity#comments" title="See comments for this post">
				Write Comment</a></span>
				<span class="post-category"><a href="http://sweatnspice.com/category/promotion" title="View all posts in Promotion" rel="category tag">Promotion</a></span>
			</h4>
			</div>
			
			<div class="post-content">
                                								<div class="postavatar">
								<img src="http://sweatnspice.com//wp-content/plugins/post-avatar/images/tongueburner.gif" width="60" height="81" alt="talk-show-host-drinks-hot-sauce-for-charity" />
<br />
                                <span class="author">Posted By:<br />TongueBurner</span></div>
                                			<p><a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/downloads/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/photo_281_3_bonnie_hunt-400x502.jpg');"  href="http://sweatnspice.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/photo_281_3_bonnie_hunt-400x502.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-2619" title="photo_281_3_bonnie_hunt-400x502" src="http://sweatnspice.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/photo_281_3_bonnie_hunt-400x502-239x300.jpg" alt="" width="239" height="300" /></a>Actress/TV talk show host <a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/www.aceshowbiz.com/news/view/w0002187.html');"  href="http://www.aceshowbiz.com/news/view/w0002187.html" target="_blank">Bonnie Hunt chugged a bottle of hot sauce</a> to raise &#8220;a quick few hundred dollars&#8221; for a research hospital earlier this month, entertainment blog Aceshowbiz.com reported.</p>
<p>The actress, best known for roles in &#8220;Beethoven,&#8221; &#8220;Jumanji&#8221; and &#8220;Jerry Maguire,&#8221; was challenged by her staff and producer to first drink from and then finish the hot sauce, the brand name of which was not reported by the blog. Hunt accepted and completed the challenge to raise funds for Robert H. Lurie Medical Research Center at Northwestern University just outside Chicago. She matched the amount raised by her staff, the blog reported.</p>
<p>While she also threw milk in her face to cool off afterward, <a href="http://sweatnspice.com/" target="_blank">Sweat &#8216;N Spice</a> is thinking her sauce of choice was no stronger than <a href="http://sweatnspice.com/products-page?heat_scale=Heat2.png" target="_blank">two peppers (on the SNS Scale)</a>. If she tried <a href="http://sweatnspice.com/products-page?heat_scale=Heat3.png" target="_blank">three pepper hot sauce </a>or <a href="http://sweatnspice.com/products-page?heat_scale=Heat4.png" target="_blank">four pepper hot sauce</a>, ASB.com would be posting her obit.</p>
			</div>
            <br style="clear: both;height: 0px;" />
		</div>

		
